        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-06T21:04:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To expand a bit on the hypothetical tests that might want to be multiprocess and with-temp-dir but that this call might be unsuitable for: (1) a test that needs to wait on the child process’ entire descendant tree instead of just its immediate children; (2) a test that wants a temp dir but only for the child process’ use, where the child spawns grandchildren that outlive it but don’t care about the temp dir.\n\n(1) sure could be a real thing. I don’t know how likely (2) is because the grandchildren would be leaks and we’d like to avoid those. The fact that you wrote WaitForAllChildProcessesOf() to consider only direct children and not all descendants tells me that there may be something to this, though. (This whole thing is a hypothesis anyway, so another shot in the dark: maybe the OS starts long-lived children on your behalf?)",
      "revId": "8cedea10186ac999991887766515b615281d7a21",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "49171ecc_fda1ae43",
        "filename": "test/win/win_multiprocess_with_tempdir.cc",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 81,
      "author": {
        "id": 1177549
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-07T14:07:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "On (1) there really isn\u0027t any way to do that without race on Windows, unless the tree you want to wait on is known to have well-defined lifetime behavior such that all parents outlive children.\nI don\u0027t think we need to worry about Windows spawning crap on our behalf on test bots, but in general that\u0027s a real worry, between \"security\" products, corpware and 3rd party, it\u0027s pretty wild out there.",
      "parentUuid": "d02f0e6c_e7840d7d",
      "revId": "8cedea10186ac999991887766515b615281d7a21",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
