        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-06T21:04:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In general, I don’t want to wind up at the point where each tweak on what we might need in a test requires the developer to choose the right multiprocess test subclass. But I can see that it’d be very useful to expose this functionality in this way, because it waits on the child automatically without having to give the child handle to anything else. We’ll talk more about this when I get to your question in the next file.\n\nBottom line: I think that this is “OK” but that there’s another way that would also be “OK.”",
      "revId": "8cedea10186ac999991887766515b615281d7a21",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
